The main `putnam_B2_correct` theorem is almost REAL: it depends on
`key_double_integral_pos` (analytic, sorry) and `centroid_ineq_via_double_integral`
(Fubini swap, sorry). The final `nlinarith` step would be real if the two lemmas compile.

## Summary
